⭐ .gitignore for Your Private Production Repo
This one protects secrets, deployment artifacts, systemd files, logs, caches, and anything that should never leave your machine or server.
# ============================
# PYTHON / FASTAPI PROJECT
# ============================

__pycache__/
*.pyc
*.pyo
*.pyd
*.pdb
*.egg-info/
*.egg
*.log

# Virtual environments
venv/
env/
.venv/

# ============================
# OS / EDITOR / TOOLING
# ============================

# macOS
.DS_Store

# Windows
Thumbs.db

# VSCode / JetBrains
.vscode/
.idea/

# ============================
# ENVIRONMENT / SECRETS
# ============================

.env
.env.*
*.secret
*.key
*.pem
*.crt
*.token
*.credentials
secrets.json
config.local.json

# AWS / Cloud
.aws/
*.tfstate
*.tfstate.backup

# ============================
# BUILD / OUTPUT / RUNTIME
# ============================

# Your app’s generated files
output/
input/
uploads/
cache/
tmp/
temp/
*.tmp

# Image processing artifacts
*.png
*.jpg
*.jpeg
*.webp
*.tiff

# Logs
*.log
logs/
*.sqlite3

# ============================
# NODE / FRONTEND (if present)
# ============================

node_modules/
npm-debug.log
yarn-error.log
dist/
build/

# ============================
# SYSTEMD / DEPLOYMENT
# ============================

*.service
deploy.sh
start.sh
stop.sh
restart.sh

# ============================
# MISC
# ============================

*.bak
*.old
*.swp
*.swo


This .gitignore ensures no secrets, no systemd files, no output separations, no uploaded images, and no deployment scripts ever get committed.

